&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=tamasfe.even-better-toml"&gt;Even better TOML&lt;/a&gt;: A TOML …&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Artur Barseghyan</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 03 Apr 2026 01:02:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>tag:None,2026-04-03:/gist-blog/posts/2026/04/useful-plugins-for-vscode/</guid><category>Tech</category><category>python</category><category>vs-code</category><category>vs-code-plugins</category></item><item><title>open-webui setup on macOS</title><link>/gist-blog/posts/2026/04/open-webui-setup-on-macos/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Here’s how to set up Open WebUI as a launchd service on macOS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="prerequisites"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Prerequisites&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First, install Open WebUI via uv if you haven’t already:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code bash literal-block"&gt;
uv&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;tool&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;install&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;open-webui
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="create-the-plist-file"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;1. Create the plist file&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;pre class="code sh literal-block"&gt;
cat&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.user.openwebui.plist&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt; EOF
&amp;lt;?xml version=&amp;quot;1.0&amp;quot; encoding=&amp;quot;UTF-8&amp;quot;?&amp;gt;
&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE …&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Artur Barseghyan</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 03 Apr 2026 00:21:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>tag:None,2026-04-03:/gist-blog/posts/2026/04/open-webui-setup-on-macos/</guid><category>Tech</category><category>python</category><category>open-webui</category><category>macos</category></item><item><title>Hide *.py,cover files from IDE</title><link>/gist-blog/posts/2026/04/hide-pycover-files-from-ide/</link><description>&lt;div class="section" id="vscode"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;VSCode&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Settings -&amp;gt; Text Editor -&amp;gt; Files -&amp;gt; Add Pattern: Add &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;**/*.py,cover&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="pycharm"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;PyCharm&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Editor -&amp;gt; File Types -&amp;gt; Ignored Files and Folders : Add &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;*.py,cover&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Artur Barseghyan</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 14:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>tag:None,2026-04-02:/gist-blog/posts/2026/04/hide-pycover-files-from-ide/</guid><category>Tech</category><category>python</category><category>vs-code</category><category>pycharm</category></item><item><title>Safezip - zero-dependency wrapper for secure ZIP extraction</title><link>/gist-blog/posts/2026/02/safezip-zero-dependency-wrapper-for-secure-zip-extraction/</link><description>&lt;a class="reference external image-reference" href="https://github.com/barseghyanartur/safezip"&gt;
